# 🔐 Fingerprint Screen Lock — Implementation Plan

## System Profile

| Component | Details |
|---|---|
| **OS** | Fedora 44 (kernel 7.0.9) |
| **Desktop** | GNOME on Wayland |
| **Sensor** | ELAN 04f3:0c00 (ELAN:ARM-M4) via USB |
| **Python** | 3.14.4 |
| **fprintd** | 1.94.5 (running, but **sensor not detected** — needs driver fix) |
| **libfprint** | 1.94.10 (stock — **does not support your ELAN sensor**) |

---

## ⚠️ Critical Finding: Your Sensor Needs a Custom Driver

> [!CAUTION]
> Your ELAN 04f3:0c00 fingerprint sensor is **NOT supported** by the stock `libfprint` shipped with Fedora 44. The `fprintd-list` command returns "No devices available". This is a known issue — the community has a working fix via the `elanmoc2` branch.

**This must be fixed first before any lock screen work can begin.**

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack Recommendation

### Why **Python + PyQt6** is the best choice:

| Factor | Python + PyQt6 | C++ + Qt6 | Rust + GTK4 |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Development Speed** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Fastest | ⭐⭐ Slow | ⭐⭐ Slow |
| **Animation Framework** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ QPropertyAnimation, QPainter, QGraphicsEffect | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Same | ⭐⭐⭐ Limited |
| **D-Bus Integration** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ `dbus-python` already installed | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ QtDBus | ⭐⭐⭐ zbus crate |
| **PAM Integration** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ `python3-pam` already installed | ⭐⭐⭐ Manual C binding | ⭐⭐⭐ pam crate |
| **Wayland Fullscreen** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Works well | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Same | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Works |
| **Maintainability** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Easy to modify | ⭐⭐⭐ Complex | ⭐⭐⭐ Borrow checker |
| **Already Installed** | ✅ PyQt6 6.11.0 + dbus-python + python3-pam | ❌ Need Qt6 dev headers | ❌ Need full Rust toolchain |

### ✅ Chosen Stack

```
